    "Theorem 3 (Reward and utility optimality: multi-shot scheme).",
    "Let Assumptions 3, 4, 5, and 6 hold.",
    "Then, the reward and utility optimality gaps of the policy π⋆ p (λ ⋆ p) satisfy R-OPT(π ⋆ p (λ ⋆ p)) ≤ 2 λ ⋆ p 1 L D M + β + M λ ⋆ p 1 ν + (M + β + M ∥λ ⋆ ν ∥ 1) ν U-OPT(π ⋆ p (λ ⋆ p)) ≤ 2 L D M + β + M λ ⋆ p 1 ν where L D:= L D + L 2 D /µ ⋆ D.Theorem 3 characterizes the optimality gap of the policy π ⋆ p (λ ⋆ p) regarding the reward and utility functions.",
    "The reward optimality gap R-OPT(π ⋆ p (λ ⋆ p)) and the utility optimality gap U-OPT(π ⋆ p (λ ⋆ p)) both scale with the parametrization gap ν in an order of √ ν.",
    "When the parametrization gap ν is sufficiently small, the multi-shot alignment scheme of Algorithm 1 readily generates an approximate solution to Problem (U-CA)."
